Rich Collins wrote:

&gt; Im using the current release version - 1.2.0. 
&gt; CrawlURI.getObject(String) doesn&#39;t exist.  Do I need to upgrade or can I
&gt; use the AList?

A recent change in HEAD deprecated directly accessing the alist putting 
it behind &#39;getObject&#39; type accessors.   Previous to this, it used to 
read CrawlURI.getAList().getObject(String).  You&#39;ll need to upgrade to 
the HEAD of Heritrix to get the former type of accessor.  Otherwise, 
there is no difference in their behaviors: Both accomplish the same 
thing adding an Object to a hash.
Hope this helps.
